The use of the 'ss' command (socket statistics) is useful in cases where the connections are overflowing the allow metric:

ss (socket statistics)

-a = all
-l = listening
-p = process
-s = summary
-4 = ipv4
-t = tcp
-u = udp
-n = resolve names
-r = resolve names

Useful links:

